    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - POWER STEERING PUMP: VICKERS (LUK) V10NF AND V20NF - INSTALL - GEAR DRIVEN PUMP
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>GEAR DRIVEN PUMP</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fasten pump, along with gasket, on engine front cover. Tighten to 30 to 38 ft-lbs. (41 to 52
                Nm).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install pressure line, return line and remote mounted reservoir hose to pump.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill system with approved power steering fluid.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Bleed system. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s05005s_22.xml" xrefid="hl0500504">LUBRICATION/ BLEED SYSTEM</hotlnk>
                on this page.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Recheck fluid level after bleeding system.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
